<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sri Lanka-Rebels Killed, 1st Ld-Writethru,0289 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PRECEDE Vavuniya
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Military says 14 Tamil rebels killed in sea battle &QL; 
 &UR; Eds: NEW throughout. CHANGES overline, dateline. No pickup. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) _ The Sri Lankan Defense Ministry said
Saturday its navy killed 14 Tamil Tiger rebels and destroyed rebel
equipment during a sea battle.
	   Military spokesman Colonel Ranjith Witana said among the
deceased were nine senior members of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam, the rebel group fighting government forces for an
independent homeland for the minority Tamils.
	   The ministry's statement came after the clandestine Voice of
Tigers radio admitted losing 12 members Friday, including two top
ranking local guerrilla leaders, in the same incident. But it said
the fatalities occurred when their speeding motorboat capsized
after an accident.
	   The Voice of Tigers radio monitored in the northern city of
Vavuniya said two lieutenant colonels were among the dead. It gave
no other details and did not say when or exactly where the accident
took place. The military also did not specify where the attack took
place.
	   Witana quoting unidentified sources said a total of 14 rebels
were killed, including nine senior rebels. He said the attack
``destroyed a large logistic consignment'' of the rebels. He did
not clarify or elaborate.
	   The rebels are fighting for a separate homeland in north and
east of Sri Lanka, accusing the Sinhalese majority of oppressing
Tamils.
	   While not all Tamils embrace the rebels' extreme solution, many
feel they are denied opportunity by the Sinhalese, who dominate the
government and military. The government denies the charge and says
Tamils have equal rights.
</TEXT>
