<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sri Lanka-Cake Theft,0136 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Christmas cakes stolen in Colombo suburb
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) _ Hundreds of residents of a Colombo
suburb had an unpleasant Christmas surprise when they discovered
that thieves had broken into a baker's shop and stolen 800 cakes,
news report said Saturday.
	   The theft occurred in the Handela area on Christmas eve, The
Island newspaper reported.
	   Many Christians in Sri Lanka give ingredients to bakers who then
prepare cakes for a small fee. The baker in Handela had taken
orders for 800 cakes, baked them and then gone to sleep after a
hard day of work.
	   On Christmas day, when the people came to collect their cakes,
they found the shop empty and the baker crying. They were told
their Christmas cakes were all stolen. The baker has notified the
police.
</TEXT>
