w1693 &Cx1f; wstm-
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Sports-Cricket-Austra 2ndLd-Writethru   12-26 0292
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Cricket-Australia-England, 2nd Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Australia wins toss but rain washes out first day
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with no play possible on first day &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MELBOURNE, Australia (AP) _ Australian paceman Matthew Nicholson
and England wicketkeeper Warren Hegg were kept waiting for their
test cricket debuts Saturday when the opening day of the fourth
test was washed out.
	   Australian captain Mark Taylor won the toss and sent England
into bat on a grassy wicket at the Melbourne Cricket Ground.
	   But heavy, persistent rain prevented any play on the opening day
and the umpires abandoned the day at 1615 local time.
	   Taylor made utility bowler Colin Miller his 12th man while
England dropped batsman John Crawley and off-spinner Peter Such.
	   England's Alec Stewart gets a reprieve from his triple
responsibilities of captaincy, batting and wicketkeeping with Hegg
coming in to take over the gloves.
	   Veteran seamer Angus Fraser got a surprise recall, ahead of
youngster Alex Tudor, as part of a four-pronged pace attack.
	   Australia has an unbeatable 2-0 lead in the five-test series and
the opening test was drawn when rain fell with the hosts in a
winning position. Play is scheduled to start half an hour early on
the next four days to help make up for lost time.
	   Australia: Mark Taylor (captain), Michael Slater, Justin Langer,
Mark Waugh, Steve Waugh, Darren Lehmann, Ian Healy, Damien Fleming,
Stuart MacGill, Matthew Nicholson, Glenn McGrath. 12th man: Colin
Miller.
	   England: Alec Stewart (captain), Michael Atherton, Nasser
Hussain, Mark Butcher, Mark Ramprakash, Graeme Hick, Warren Hegg,
Dean Headley, Darren Gough, Angus Fraser, Alan Mullally. 12th man:
John Crawley.
 &UR; (tjh)
