</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-China-Mao Tse-tung </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
China commemorates 105th anniversary of Mao's birth
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ China marked the 105th anniversary of the birth
of the late revolutionary leader Mao Tse-tung on Saturday with the
release of books, computer disks and other memorabilia.
	   Although many of Mao's radical communist policies have been
discredited since his death in 1976, the ruling Communist Party has
sought to use his legacy to reinforce its own legitimacy.
	   Wei Jianxing, a member of the Standing Committee of the party's
powerful Politburo, presided over the launching of a CD ROM
introducing Mao's theories illustrated by more than 3,000 pictures
from official archives, the newspaper China Daily and other
state-run media reported.
	   A six-volume reference work on Mao's life also was recently
published, the reports said.
</TEXT>
