<SLUG> BC-Lebanon-Israel </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Officer of Israeli-allied militia found shot dead
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MARJAYOUN, Lebanon AP) - A security officer of the
Israeli-allied South Lebanon Army militia was found dead of gunshot
wounds Saturday in the village of Chebaa, Lebanese security
officials said.
	   The body of Ghassan Daher was found in the early morning shortly
after a shootout in the village in the western Bekaa valley, said
the officials, speaking on the customary condition of anonymity.
	   It could not be determined whether Daher's killing resulted from
a personal vendetta or a political assassination, the officials
said.
	   Chebaa is on the slopes of Mount Hermon in the Israeli-occupied
zone in south Lebanon, which is patrolled by some 1,500 Israeli
troops and 2,500 allied Lebanese militiamen. It is a center for
smuggling contraband goods between Lebanon, Israel and Syria.
	   Hezbollah, the Iranian-backed guerrilla group whose fighters are
active in the region, often target collaborators with Israel. A
Hezbollah official in Beirut said the group had no comment on
Daher's killing.
