<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Armenia-Leader Buried </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Prominent Armenian nationalist buried Saturday
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   YEREVAN, Armenia (AP) _ The former leader of a secretive
nationalist party was buried in Yerevan's most honored cemetery on
Saturday, five years after he was sent into exile.
	   Grair Marukhian, who led the Dashnak Party from the mid-1980s
until he went into a coma in 1994, died Monday in Athens, Greece.
His body was brought back to Armenia for burial.
	   In 1993, then-President Levon Ter-Petrosian exiled Marukhian,
and suspended the party the following year. Armenia's Supreme Court
banned the party in 1995 but allowed it to resume operations
earlier this year.
	   Dashnak, the Armenian Revolutionary Federation, is Armenia's
oldest political grouping. It was founded as a secret organization
in 1890 to fight for a united, independent Armenia.
	   (str/nw/ji) 	   
</TEXT>
