<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Juventus-Sukur, 1st Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Turkish reports say Juve offering dlrs 12 million for Sukur
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; EDS: SUBS 5th graf, Sukur joined, to CORRECT Turin club to Torino &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ANKARA, Turkey (AP) _ Italian club Juventus has made a dlrs-12
million offer to entice Galatasaray striker Hakan Sukur, news
reports said Saturday.
	   Istanbul club Galatasaray, suffering from a financial crisis,
left the decision up to Sukur, daily Hurriyet said.
	   But sports daily Foto Mac reported that Sukur was not eager to
go back to Italy.
	   ``I already closed the Italian venture,'' Foto Mac quoted Sukur
as saying. ``I want to conclude my soccer career in a Galatasaray
uniform.''
	   Sukur joined Galatasaray three years ago after a brief stint
with Turin club Torino. He scored 32 league goals last season for
the reigning champion Galatasaray.
	   Juventus top manager Luciano Moggi reportedly traveled to
Istanbul to discuss the transfer of Sukur, another sports daily,
Fanatik said.
	   Juventus club offices were closed Saturday, a national holiday
in Italy. In Turkey, Galatasaray officials were not available for
comment.
	   (sh-fd)
</TEXT>
