<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Dortmund-Lehmann </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Dortmund gets Inter keeper Jens Lehmann
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   DORTMUND, Germany (AP) _ Borussia Dortmund announced Saturday
the Bundesliga club has ended months of effort by finally getting
Inter Milan keeper Jens Lehmann.
	   The German international, a backup at the Italian club, will
transfer for 7 million marks (dlrs 4.3 million) and sign a
three-year contract.
	   Lehmann replaces his national team rival Stefan Klos, who agreed
to terms with the Glasgow Rangers shortly before Christmas.
	   The 29-year-old Lehmann stayed in Italy just four months after
transferring over the summer from Schalke, where he was one of the
heroes in the German club's 1997 UEFA Cup triumph.
	   Lehmann chafed over being benched in favor of Sebastiano Rossi
at Inter after just a few matches.
	   ``I can't take it anymore. I'm not willing to have an existence
as Rossi' subsitute,'' Lehmann told the German sports agnecy SID.
	   Veteran defender Juergen Kohler, another former Serie A player,
extended his contract at Dortmund another year until June 30, 2000.
	    &UR; (rk)	   
</TEXT>
