<HEADLINE>
Bodies of four kidnapped foreigners found in Chechnya
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: UPDATES with report unconfirmed by federal law enforcement
bodies. &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ The bodies of four foreigners beheaded in Chechnya
earlier this month were found on the outskirts of the Chechen
capital Grozny, a news report said Saturday.
	   The bodies of the four men _ Peter Kennedy, Darren Hickey and
Rudolf Petschi of Britain, and New Zealand's Stanley Shaw _ were
found late Friday night, said Chechen presidential spokesman
Mairbek Vachagayev, according to the ITAR-Tass news agency.
	   However, Russia's Interior Ministry has been unable to confirm
the report.
