<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Greece-Albania-Premier's Baby </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Albanian premier's baby flown to Greece for treatment
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ATHENS, Greece (AP) _ The prematurely-born baby of Albanian
Premier Pandeli Majko was due to be flown to Greece for treatment
Saturday because of poor medical facilities in Albania, news
reports said.
	   The baby boy, born one month premature on Friday, was to be
transported to Athens on a Greek military transport plane,
accompanied by Majko's 28-year-old wife, the reports said.
	   Doctors said the baby suffered a respiratory infection and that
his condition was stable.
	   Hospitals in Albania, Europe's poorest country, lack many basic
facilities.
	   Majko, a 30-year-old senior official of the governing Socialist
party, became premier three months ago after his predecessor, Fatos
Nano, resigned amid political turmoil.
 &UR; dg
</TEXT>
