<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-British Roundup, 1st Add </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LONDON: from the end.
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Details of English Premier League games:
 &UR; Arsenal 1 West Ham 0 (1-0) &QC; 
	   Marc Overmars scored the only goal of the game after eight
minutes, beating two players on the left and cutting inside before
shooting home from just inside the area. Ian Wright, playing
against Arsenal for the first time since his move to West Ham, had
few chances to shine as the Gunners dominated.
 &UR; Coventry 1 Tottenham 1 (0-1) &QC; 
	   Defender Sol Campbell turned the ball home in the 17th minute
after Les Ferdinand had touched on a corner by Darren Anderton.
John Aloisi came off the bench 16 minutes from the end to score the
equalizer in the 81st.
 &UR; Everton 0 Derby 0 &QC; 
	   Everton made it six goal-less draws out of 10 home games in the
Premier League this season. Derby's Estonian goalkeeper, Mort Poom,
fumbled a 20-meter free kick from Olivier Decourt and then
recovered to dive at the feet of Danny Cadamarteri. And Everton's
Norwegian 'keeper Thomas Myhre cleared the ball straight to Derby's
Jacob Laursen while well off his line and was glad to see the Dane
miss an empty net from 35 meters.
 &UR; Manchester United 3 Nottingham Forest 0 (1-0) &QC; 
	   Ronny Johnsen gave United a 28th minute lead with a header from
David Beckham's corner. Johnsen made it 2-0 with a close range shot
in the 59th minute after Henning Berg had headed across the face of
the goal. Three minutes later it was 3-0 when Ryan Giggs lobbed the
ball over Forest 'keeper David Beasant from Paul Scholes' pass.
Forest, without suspended striker Pierre van Hooijdonk, tied its
worst of 16 Premier League games without a win.
 &UR; Middlesbrough 1 Liverpool 3 (1-2) &QC; 
	   Liverpool defender Jamie Carragher slid the ball home in a
scramble in front of goal in the 17th minute after Paul Ince had
headed on a corner. Brian Deane leveled in the 32nd minute from
Paul Gascoigne's well-placed free kick. Liverpool regained the lead
through Jamie Redknapp after a short free kick inside the box in
the 35th minute. It was awarded when Boro goalkeeper Mark Schwarzer
was forced to handle a poor back pass from Gary Pallister. Vegard
Heggem scored the third two minutes from the end after a 30-meter
break.
 &UR; Newcastle 0 Leeds 3 (0-1) &QC; 
	   Harry Kewell scored with the first Leeds shot on target after 38
minutes. Lee Bowyer prodded the second in the 62nd after
Newcastle's Irish international goalkeeper Shay Given had fumbled a
shot from Kewell. Jimmy Floyd Hasselbaink scored again in the final
minute, turning past defender Steve Howey before shooting home.
 &UR; Sheffield Wednesday 0 Leicester 1 (0-1) &QC; 
	   Tony Cottee fired Leicester ahead with an angled shot in the
34th minute after a weak back pass from England international Andy
Hinchcliffe.
 &UR; Southampton 0 Chelsea 2 (0-1) &QC; 
	   Gianfranco Zola floated over a cross from the left for Tore
Andre Flo to volley home after 20 minutes. Three minutes into the
second half, Saints goalkeeper Paul Jones palmed a cross from Dan
Petrescu into the path of Gustavo Poyet who slotted the ball into
an empty net.
 &UR; Wimbledon 2 Charlton 1 (1-1) &QC; 
	   Neil Redfearn fired Charlton ahead after 29 minutes with a
curling, 25-meter shot but Wimbledon turned the game around. Four
minutes later, Jason Euell leveled with a close range shot from
Michael Hughes' cross and Hughes fired the winner six minutes into
the second half after a layoff from Carl Leaburn.
	   (rjm)	   
</TEXT>
