<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Kazakstan-Oil </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Kazakstan plans its own oil tanker fleet
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ The Kazak government plans to create a fleet of
tankers to ship oil abroad, the ITAR-Tass news agency reported
Saturday.
	   The government will spend dlrs 94 million on purchasing tankers
from other countries or construction of the ships at its own Zenit
defense plant in Uralsk, northwestern Kazakstan.
	   The tankers will ply the Volga River, Black Sea, Bosporus Strait
and the Mediterranean, ITAR-Tass said.
	   (ji) 	   
</TEXT>
