<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,1250 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   Variably cloudy skies prevailed across the U.S. Virgin islands
and Puerto Rico during the afternoon hours. Scattered passing
showers were noted, but they were most prevalent over the interior
sections of Puerto Rico. High temperatures ranged from the lower
70s over the mountains to mostly in the 80s elsewhere. It was
breezy, with gusty east to northeast winds of 15 to 25 mph.
	   There will be varying amounts of cloudiness across the region
tonight. Scattered showers will occur, especially over the U.S.
Virgin Islands, the east half of Puerto Rico and across the coastal
waters. Low temperatures will range from 60 to 65 over the normal
cool spots of Puerto Rico to generally between 65 and 75 degrees
elsewhere. The winds will be east to northeast at 10 to 20 mph,
except less in sheltered areas.
	   Mid to upper-level high pressure centered north-northeast of the
U.S. Virgin Islands and Puerto Rico late this Saturday afternoon
will move east through Sunday. A low to mid-level trough located
over the Leeward Islands will approach the local area this evening,
passing across the region late tonight and Sunday. This will result
in an increase in cloudiness, showers and isolated thunderstorms
over the area for Sunday through Monday.
 &UR; San Juan and north sections of Puerto Rico
	   Tonight ... Variable cloudiness with a 40 percent chance of
showers. Low 70 to 75. Wind mainly east 5 to 15 mph.
	   Sunday ... Variable cloudiness with a 50 percent chance of
showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. Becoming breezy in the
afternoon. High 80 to 85. Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 mph
early, becoming east and increasing to 15 to 20 mph and gusty in
the afternoon.
	   Sunday night ... Mostly cloudy and breezy with showers likely.
Chance of a thunderstorm. Low 70 to 75. Chance of rain 60 percent.
	   Monday ... Considerable cloudiness and breezy with showers
likely. Chance of a thunderstorm. High 80 to 85. Chance of rain 60
percent.
 &UR; East sections of Puerto Rico
	   Tonight ... Variable cloudiness with a 50 percent chance of
showers. Low 70 to 75. Wind mainly east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Sunday ... Variable cloudiness with a 50 percent chance of
showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. Becoming breezy in the
afternoon. High 80 to 85. Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 mph
early, becoming east and increasing to 15 to 20 mph and gusty in
the afternoon.
	   Sunday night ... Mostly cloudy and breezy with showers likely.
Chance of a thunderstorm. Low 70 to 75. Chance of rain 60 percent.
	   Monday ... Considerable cloudiness and breezy with showers
likely. Chance of a thunderstorm. High 80 to 85. Chance of rain 60
percent.
 &UR; Ponce and south sections of Puerto Rico
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy. A 30 percent chance of showers,
mainly east. Low 65 to 75. Wind mainly northeast 10 mph or less.
	   Sunday ... Variable cloudiness with a 40 percent chance of
showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. Becoming breezy in the
afternoon. High 80 to 90. Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 mph
early, becoming east and increasing to 15 to 20 mph and gusty in
the afternoon.
	   Sunday night ... Mostly cloudy and breezy with showers likely.
Chance of a thunderstorm. Low 70 to 75. Chance of rain 60 percent.
	   Monday ... Considerable cloudiness and breezy with showers
likely. Chance of a thunderstorm. High 80 to 85. Chance of rain 60
percent.
 &UR; Mayaguez and west sections of Puerto Rico
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy with a 20 percent chance of showers.
Low 65 to 75. Wind mainly east 5 to 15 mph.
	   Sunday ... Variable cloudiness with a 50 percent chance of
showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. Becoming breezy in the
afternoon. High 80 to 90. Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 mph
early, becoming east and increasing to 15 to 20 mph and gusty in
the afternoon.
	   Sunday night ... Mostly cloudy and breezy with a 50 percent
chance of showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. Low 70 to 75.
	   Monday ... Considerable cloudiness and breezy with showers
likely. Chance of a thunderstorm. High 80 to 85. Chance of rain 60
percent.
 &UR; Interior sections of Puerto Rico
	   Tonight ... Partly cloudy. A 40 percent chance of showers,
mainly east. Low 60 to 70. Wind mainly east 5 to 15 mph.
	   Sunday ... Variable cloudiness with a 50 percent chance of
showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. Becoming breezy in the
afternoon. High from near 70 mountains to 80 to 85 lower
elevations. Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 mph early, becoming
east and increasing to 15 to 25 mph and gusty in the afternoon.
	   Sunday night ... Mostly cloudy and breezy with showers likely.
Chance of a thunderstorm. Low 60 to 70. Chance of rain 60 percent.
	   Monday ... Considerable cloudiness and breezy with showers
likely. Chance of a thunderstorm. High from near 70 mountains to
near 80 lower elevations. Chance of rain 60 percent.
 &UR; St. Thomas, St. John and St. Croix
	   Tonight ... Variable cloudiness with a 50 percent chance of
showers. Low 70 to 75. Wind east 10 to 15 mph.
	   Sunday ... Variable cloudiness with a 50 percent chance of
showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. Becoming breezy by
afternoon. High 80 to 85. Wind east to southeast 10 to 15 mph
early, becoming east and increasing to 15 to 20 mph and gusty by
afternoon.
	   Sunday night ... Mostly cloudy and breezy with showers likely.
Chance of a thunderstorm. Low 70 to 75. Chance of rain 60 percent.
	   Monday ... Considerable cloudiness and breezy with showers
likely. Chance of a thunderstorm. High 80 to 85. Chance of rain 60
percent.
 &UR; Puerto Rico and U.S. Virgin islands waters
	   Synopsis ... Surface high pressure centered over the north
central Atlantic extending southwest to the Bahamas will continue
to produce a moderate to strong trade wind flow across the local
waters through Sunday night. A low to mid level trough over the
Leeward Islands late this afternoon will approach the local region
this evening, passing across the waters late tonight and Sunday.
 &UR; Atlantic waters
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   Tonight ... Wind mainly east 15 to 25 kt and gusty. Nearshore
seas 6 to 7 ft and off shore seas 7 to 10 ft, east-northeast.
Scattered showers.
	   Sunday ... Wind east to southeast around 15 kt early, becoming
east and increasing to 15 to 25 kt and gusty in the afternoon.
Nearshore seas 6 to 7 ft and off shore seas 7 to 10 ft east swells.
Scattered showers.
	   Sunday night ... Wind east 15 to 25 kt and gusty. Nearshore seas
6 to 8 ft and off shore seas 8 to 11 ft east swells. Scattered to
numerous showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
 &UR; Caribbean waters
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   Tonight ... Wind mainly east 15 to 25 kt and gusty. Nearshore
seas 6 to 7 ft and off shore and Anegada Passage seas 7 to 10 ft
east swells. Scattered showers.
	   Sunday ... Wind east to southeast around 15 kt early, becoming
east and increasing to 15 to 25 kt and gusty in the afternoon.
Nearshore seas 6 to 7 ft and off shore and Anegada Passage seas 7
to 10 ft east swells. Scattered showers.
	   Sunday night ... Wind east 15 to 25 kt and gusty. Nearshore seas
6 to 8 ft and off shore seas 8 to 11 ft east swells. Scattered to
numerous showers. Isolated thunderstorms. 	   
</TEXT>
