<HEADLINE>
Southern beats Bethune-Cookman 28-2 in U.S. college Heritage Bowl
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: To be LEAD with results of Missouri vs West Virginia in
Insight.com Bowl &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   ATLANTA (AP) _ Ryan Lewis ran 57 yards for a touchdown in the
third quarter and added a 13-yard scoring run, leading Southern to
a 28-2 victory over Bethune-Cookman as the two U.S. college teams
met in Saturday's Heritage Bowl.
	   Lewis finished with 84 yards on seven carries. Steve Wofford
gained 119 yards on 27 carries for Southern and had an 11-yard
scoring run in the first quarter.
	   The Jaguars (9-3) were making their fourth straight Heritage
Bowl appearance as the Southwestern Athletic Conference
representative. Southern has won four of five appearances overall
in the battle of historically black colleges in the Georgia Dome.
	   But they gave up a second-quarter safety, when Wofford was
tackled in the end zone for a 2-yard loss by Abdul Yates, and
struggled on offense until Lewis took a pitch, cut back through the
line, then raced down the right sideline, giving Southern a 14-2
lead 2:10 into the second half.
	   The Wildcats (8-3), making their first postseason appearance in
21 years as the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference representative, had
seven fumbles and four interceptions.
	   They lost starting quarterback Pa'tell Troutman to a knee sprain
in the second quarter. Backup quarterback Randell Foster was
intercepted four times, including Jerry Guye's 35-yard touchdown
return in the fourth quarter. Defensive back Jackie Mitchell had
two interceptions.
