<SLUG> BC-Sports-Basketball-US College Roundup,0291 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Louisville beats No.3 Kentucky in U.S. college basketball
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LOUISVILLE, Kentucky (AP) _ Marques Maybin scored 19 points,
including seven straight late in the second half, as Louisville
upset No. 3 Kentucky 83-74 for the second straight season Saturday.
	   The Wildcats (10-3), coming off a 71-60 loss to second-ranked
Duke Tuesday, hadn't lost consecutive games since falling to
Arkansas and Syracuse during the 1994 season.
	   The Cardinals (5-2) also surprised Kentucky last year, beating
the heavily favored Wildcats 79-76 in Rupp Arena.
	   Kentucky lost only three games all last season en route to its
second NCAA championship in three years. The Cardinals couldn't
match their performance against the Wildcats and finished 12-20,
only the second losing season in coach Denny Crum's 27 seasons.
	   Cameron Murray and Tony Williams each added 14 points as
Louisville, banned from postseason play by the NCAA earlier this
year, won its third consecutive game.
	   ___
 &UR; No. 16 Clemson 67, Furman 54
	   In Greenville, South Carolina, Harold Jamison had 16 points and
16 rebounds, and Vincent Whitt scored 11 of his 13 points in the
second half as No. 16 Clemson beat Furman 67-54 Saturday.
	   Jamison was 7-of-10 from the field for the Tigers (11-1), who
beat the Paladins (6-4) for the 23rd straight time. It was the
first basketball game at the new Bi-Lo Center, a dlrs 63 million
arena that opened in September.
	   Furman pulled within 43-41 in the second half on a 3-pointer by
Kyle Julius, but Jamison's putback with 12:21 left started a 22-4
run by Clemson.
	   Whitt scored seven points and Clemson's top scorer, Terrell
McIntyre, added two baskets during the streak.
</TEXT>
