<SLUG> BC-Lebanon-Dancer Shot </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Prominent Lebanese dancer shot dead
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) _ The well-known Lebanese belly dancer
Danny Bustros died of a gunshot wound to the head Saturday, police
said.
	   Bustros, who was in her early forties, died in a hospital north
of Beirut from a brain hemorrhage caused by a pistol bullet.
	   Police were investigating the death to see whether it was a case
of suicide or murder, a policeman said, speaking on condition of
anonymity.
	   The private television channel Murr reported that police were
questioning a male foreigner and a Filipino maid who were at
Bustros' house, north of Beirut, when the shooting occurred.
	   The channel did not elaborate.
	   Bustros, who came from a prominent Lebanese Christian family,
began her dancing career at a young age.
	   She was well known in the Arab world for mixing traditional Arab
belly dancing with her own modern style of dancing.
	   Her most famous role was in a musical based on the opera Carmen
that was staged in 1996 and featured the Lebanese singer Melhem
Barakat.
