<HEADLINE>
One dead, two missing, as gales, rain lash Britain and Ireland
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: EDITS to correct one confirmed dead, with two feared dead ,

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Police in Britain and Ireland said Saturday that
one man was dead with two more feared dead and several injured as
both countries were battered by high wind and rain.
	   Police said one man was killed in County Galway, western
Ireland, when a falling tree crushed his car.
	   In Brighton, southern England, coastguard officials said that a
28-year-old man was swept into the sea by a 30 foot (9 meter) wave
as he walked along beach with his girlfriend and a child. A rescue
attempt later failed to winch him to safety.
	   Neither police force immediately gave identities for the men.
	   In Devon, southwest Britain, witnesses said they saw a
44-year-old man swept away by flood waters in his garden.
	   ``It is a strong probability that he fell into the water. He was
near some broken fencing and it's thought he was carried away by
the strong current,'' Devon and Cornwall Police said.
