returns to the top of the Premier League with a 2-0 victory at
struggling Southampton on Saturday as Aston Villa goes down 2-1 at
another lowly team, Blackburn Rovers.
	   Slug Sports-Soccer-British Roundup. Has moved.
	   By Robert Millward.
 &UR; CRICKET:
	   WELLINGTON, New Zealand _ New Zealand resumes on 51-1 Sunday on
the second day of the second cricket test against India, with
India's 208 first-innings' total the home side's first target.
	   BC-Sports-Cricket-New Zealand-India. Expected by 0800 GMT.
	   By Ihithisham Kamardeen.
	   MELBOURNE, Australia _ If the weatherman cooperates, England and
Australia hope to get the fourth Ashes test under way Sunday after
rain washed out the opening day at the Melbourne Cricket Ground.
	   BC-Sports-Cricket-Australia-England. Expected by 0900 GMT.
	   DURBAN, South Africa _ The West Indies batsmen fail to grasp the
initiative as South Africa dismisses them for 198 on the first day
of the third test at Kingsmead Saturday. At the close of play,
South Africa is on 46 without loss.
