<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-1999-Calendar,0928 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EDS: Some dates and sites are provisional and subject to change.)
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; 1999 World Sports Calendar &QC; 
 &UR; By The Associated Press &QC; 
 &UR; JANUARY &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   1 _ Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Germany _ ski jumping, FIS, Nordic
World Cup, Four Hills, 115K Hill.
	   1 _ Tampa, Florida _ American football, NCAA, Outback Bowl.
	   1 _ Jacksonville, Florida _ American football, NCAA, Gator Bowl.
	   1 _ Orlando, Florida _ American football, NCAA, Citrus Bowl.
	   1 _ Dallas _ American football, NCAA, Cotton Bowl.
	   1 _ Pasadena, California _ American football, NCAA, Rose Bowl.
	   1 _ New Orleans _ American football, NCAA, Sugar Bowl.
	   1-May 7 _ various sites _ rugby union, IRB, repechage playoff
for two remaining spots in 20-team World Cup.
	   1-3 _ Maribor, Slovenia _ skiing, women, FIS, super-G, giant
slalom, slalom World Cup.
	   2 _ Durham, England _ athletics, IAAF, Durham Cross-Country
Invitational.
	   2 _ Miami _ American football, NCAA, Orange Bowl.
	   2-3 _ New York _ American football, NFL, NFL Wild Card playoffs.
	   2-6 _ Sydney, Australia _ cricket, ICC, Australia vs. England,
fifth test.
	   2-6 _ Hamilton, New Zealand _ cricket, ICC, New Zealand vs.
India, third test.
	   2-6 _ Cape Town, South Africa _ cricket, ICC, South Africa vs.
West Indies, fourth test.
	   3 _ Innsbruck, Austria _ ski jumping, FIS, Nordic World Cup,
Four Hills, 110K Hill.
	   3 _ Schonach, Germany _ skiing, FIS, Nordic Combined World Cup.
	   3-6 _ Tiers, Italy _ luge, FIL, World Cup (natural track)
	   3-9 _ Perth, Australia _ tennis, men, women, exhibition, Hopman
Cup.
	   3-9 _ Gold Coast, Australia _ tennis, women, WTA, Australian
Women's Hardcourt Championships.
	   4 _ Tempe, Arizona _ American football, NCAA, Fiesta Bowl.
	   4-9 _ Auckland, New Zealand _ tennis, women, WTA, ABS Bank
Classic.
	   4-10 _ Adelaide, Australia _ tennis, men, ATP Tour, AAPT
Championships.
	   4-10 _ Doha, Qatar _ tennis, men, ATP Tour event.
	   5 _ Reit im Winkl, Germany _ skiing, FIS, Nordic Combined World
Cup.
	   5 _ New York _ baseball, U.S. Baseball Hall of Fame voting
announced.
	   5-6 _ Otepaa, Estonia _ skiing, men, women, FIS, Nordic World
Cup, cross-country, men's 15-km freestyle; women's 10-km freestyle.
	   5-6 _ Kranjska Gora, Slovenia _ skiing, men, FIS, giant slalom,
slalom World Cup.
	   5-6 _ Beijing, China _ swimming, FINA, World Cup.
	   5-7 _ Morzine, France _ snowboarding, FIS, World Cup, giant
slalom and halfpipe.
	   6 _ Bischofshofen, Austria _ ski jumping, FIS, Nordic World Cup,
Four Hills, 120K Hill.
	   6-7 _ Avoriaz-Morzine-Le Gets, France _ snowboarding, men,
women, FIS, World Cup.
	   7-9 _ Schladming, Austria _ skiing, men, FIS, slalom, super-G
World Cup.
	   7-10 _ Melbourne, Australia _ golf, men, Australasian PGA,
Victorian Open, Melbourne, Australia.
	   7-10 _ Lahaina, Hawaii _ golf, men, U.S. PGA Tour, Mercedes
Championships.
	   7-22 _ Melbourne, Australia _ sailing, ISAF, 1999 Sailing
Worlds.
	   8-9 _ Berchtesgaden, Germany _ skiing, women, FIS, slalom, giant
slalom World Cup.
	   8-10 _ Heerenveen, Netherlands _ speedskating, ISU, European
Speed Skating Championships.
	   8-10 _ Nagano, Japan _ speedskating, ISU, World Championships
qualifying event.
	   8-10 _ Milwaukee, Wisconsin _ speedskating, ISU, World
Championships qualifying event.
	   8-10 _ Oberhof, Germany _ biathlon, men, women, IBU, World Cup.
	   8-10 _ Hanover, New Hampshire _ athletics, NCAA, Dartmouth
Indoor Relays.
	   9 _ Auckland, New Zealand _ cricket, ICC, New Zealand vs. India,
first one-day international.
	   9-10 _ Mt. Tremblant, Quebec (Canada) _ skiing, men, women, FIS,
Freestyle World Cup, moguls and aerials.
	   9-10 _ Strbske Pleso, Slovakia _ skiing, FIS, Nordic Combined
World Cup
	   9-10 _ Engelberg, Switzerland _ ski jumping, FIS, Nordic World
Cup, 120K Hill.
	   9-10 _ Hong Kong _ swimming, FINA, World Cup.
	   9-10 _ New York _ American football, NFL, NFL Divisional
playoffs.
	   9-12 _ Nove Mesto, Czech Republic _ skiing, men, women, FIS,
Nordic World Cup, cross-country, men's 15-km classic, 4x10-km
relay, 30-km freestyle; women's 10-km classic, 4x5-km relay, 15-km
freestyle.
	   10 _ Flachau, Austria _ skiing, men, FIS, giant slalom World
Cup.
	   10 _ Brisbane, Australia _ cricket, ICC, Carlton and United One
Day Series, Australia vs. England.
	   10 _ Amorebieta, Spain _ athletics, IAAF, Zornotza
Cross-Country.
	   10 _ Tokyo _ figure skating, Honda Lev Cup International Open.
	   10-24 _ Tokyo _ sumo, New Year Grand Sumo Tournament.
	   10-17 _ Berchtesgaden, Germany _ snowboarding, men, women, FIS,
World Championships.
	   11 _ Brisbane, Australia _ cricket, ICC, Carlton and United One
Day Series, England vs. Sri Lanka.
	   11-17 _ Sydney, Australia _ tennis, women, WTA, Adidas
International.
	   11-17 _ Hobart, Australia _ tennis, women, WTA, Tasmanian
International.
	   11-17 _ Sydney, Australia _ tennis, men, ATP Tour, Adidas
International.
	   11-17 _ Auckland, New Zealand _ tennis, men, ATP Tour, Heineken
Open.
	   11-17 _ Oberhof, Germany _ luge, FIL, World Cup (artificial
track).
	   12 _ Adelboden, Switzerland _ skiing, men, FIS, giant slalom
World Cup.
	   12 _ Hamilton, New Zealand _ cricket, ICC, New Zealand vs.
India, second one-day international.
	   12-16 _ Wellington, New Zealand _ diving, FINA, 11th Diving
World Cup.
	   12-17 _ Winterberg, Germany _ bobsled, FIBT, World Cup/European
Championship.
	    &UR; MORE
</TEXT>
