----APTN'S 0100 OUTLOOK FOR SUNDAY DECEMBER 26,  1998----

EXPECTED: &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
IRAQ: RAMADAN - APTV will be doing its own interview with the Iraqi
Vice President Taha Yassin Ramadan following his statement that Iraq
will fire at U-S and British aircraft in the no-fly zones over
northern and southern Iraq. (Expected First run Europe Morning 0900)
-----
IRAQ: REACTION - We will be seeking reaction to the Iraqi
announcement that US and UK planes will be shot at in the no-fly
zones in northern and southern Iraq. (TBA)
----
KOSOVO: FIGHTING - Ethnic Albanians are on the move again after a
two-day crackdown by Serb police and Yugoslav army units. Most
refugees in the area west of Podujevo made their way to Lapastica, a
village still held by the Kosovo Liberation Army. APTN is in the
area and is monitoring developments. (TBA)
-----
GERMANY: EURO - Last minute preparations in Germany for the launch
of the single European currency are under way. Many financial
institutions have had new technology installed and given staff
months of training for the moment the euro comes to life. In our
series of reports into the euro, we talk to the chief economist at
the Deutsche Bank  about the final countdown. (Expected First run
Europe 0400 )
----
INDIA: GOLD BUREAU - India's growing beauty cosmetics market is
glittering with a new  product  - that of pure gold. Beauty
therapists in New Delhi and Bombay have launched creams that use the
precious metal as an ingredient to make the skin look more glossy
and fair. (Expected First run Europe 0400 )
-----
AUSTRALIA: BALLOON - We hope to have preparations from a joint
Australian/U-S team which plans to launch another attempt to fly a
balloon around the world next week. American real estate magnate
Dave Liniger and his Remax team are making final preparations in
the Australian town of Alice Springs to launch their giant balloon
on or soon after December the 29th. (Expected First run Asia Pacific
Late 0715)
-----
RUNNING  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC;  &QC; 
----
IRAQ: US/UK PATROLS  - Iraqi Vice President Taha Yassin Ramadan told
Qatar's Al-Jazeera television Iraq will fire on warplanes patrolling
the northern and southern no-fly zones imposed after the Gulf War.
(F-l-a-s-h-e-d at 0010) This is wrapped with shots from an Iraqi TV
b-u-l-l-e-t-i-n of the presenter making the announcement that
anti-aircraft gunners drove off an attack by 'enemy' planes that
crossed into Iraq from Kuwaiti and Saudi airspace on Saturday. It
also includes shots of Saddam at a meeting of the Revolutionary
Council. (First ran 1900 Latin America)
----
RUSSIA: YELTSIN -  Russian President Boris Yeltsin vows to defend
freedom of speech in an apparent response to recent demands by the
Communists to reintroduce media censorship. APTN will have extracts
of a Yeltsin interview on Russian television. (First Run Asia
Pacific Early 1945 )
------
IRELAND: WEATHER - Bad weather has struck the island of Ireland with
storms bringing down trees and power lines, plunging parts
of the country into darkness. (First run Australia/NZ 2300)
----
MEXICO: PRISON - APTN has  pictures of a tense standoff at a prison
in Mexico City between a group of prisoners holding a dozen
hostages and police. The prisoners are threatening to kill the
hostages unless the police back off. (First Run 1600 Europe Late)
-----
UK: AMBASSADOR -  The Russian ambassador to London Yuri Fokin has
returned to Britain on Saturday to resume diplomatic relations.
Fokin had been recalled to Moscow for urgent consultations with
President Boris Yeltsin following Russian anger over the joint British and
American air strikes on Iraq. (First Run 1600 Europe Late)
----
UK:  HUNT - Across Britain, Boxing Day on December 26th marks a
traditional fox hunting day. But animal rights activists often make
their presence felt at the hunts. APTN has coverage of the hunt at
Malden in Essex where 400 protesters faced the riders. (First  Run
1600 Europe Late)
----
RUSSIA: HOLIDAYS - APTN has pictures from Russia where the Orthodox
Christmas  holiday season is beginning. Celebrations are starting
with an ice sculpture festival in Pushkin Park. (First Run 1600
Europe Late)
----
ENVIRONMENT: OIL SPILLS - An international animal welfare
organization has devised a new way to save sea birds, some of the
most common victims of oil spills. After rescue, the birds are
cleaned using a new high-tech system aimed at causing as little
stress as possible. (First Run 1600 Europe Late)
