<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Malaysia-Intruder Stabbed </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Report: Boy kills ex-convict with machete
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) _ A 15-year old armed with a machete
stabbed to death an ex-convict who barged into the boy's house on
Christmas Day, a news report said Sunday.
	   Police found the body of Aripin Salat slumped on the stairway of
the boy's house, clutching the machete in his hands, The Star daily
reported.
	   According to police, the boy and his two-year-old sister were at
home in the rural town of Sandakan on northern Borneo island when
the man, in his 30s, came by their house on Dec. 25 asking for a
cup of water, which the teenager provided.
	   The man then asked for a cigarette but the boy said his father,
who was working at a farm some distance away, wasn't able to give
him one.
	   Police said the ex-convict then barged into the house and
threatened to shoot the boy and his sister. The boy grabbed a
machete lying in the hallway, struggled with the intruder and
stabbed him at the waist.
	   The boy grabbed his sister and fled. When he returned with his
father, they found the intruder slumped in the house, the machete
still embedded in his body.
	   Police said the ex-convict was released from prison in July. 	   
</TEXT>
