<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Ice Hockey-NHL Roundup,0311 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Sabres 2, Devils 0
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   EAST RUTHERFORD, New Jersey (AP) _ Dominik Hasek continued his
December shutout surge and Miraslav Satan scored both goals as the
Buffalo Sabres beat the New Jersey Devils 2-0 Saturday night.
	   The shutout was the second straight and fourth of the month for
Hasek, who made 34 saves. Hasek, who leads the NHL with seven
shutouts, has not allowed a goal in 163:35.
	   The shutout was the 40th of Hasek's NHL career.
	   The Northeast Division-leading Sabres, 10-1-1 in their last 12
games, improved to 19-6-5 overall. The Atlantic Division-leading
Devils dropped to 19-9-4.
 &UR; Islanders 4, Bruins 2
	   In Uniondale, New York, Mike Watt and Claude Lapointe scored in
the third period to lead the New York Islanders over the Boston
Bruins.
	   Watt's shot from the left circle at 9:50 beat goalie Byron Dafoe
while two players were wrestling in front of his crease to break a
2-2 tie. Lapointe clinched the victory with a shorthanded breakaway
at 14:51.
	   Zigmund Palffy and Trevor Linden also scored for New York. Chris
Taylor and Dmitri Khristich scored for the Bruins, who have lost
two straight.
 &UR; Rangers 6, Hurricanes 3
	   In Greensboro, North Carolina, Petr Nedved had two goals and two
assists, and the New York Rangers scored six times in the second
period for a victory over the Carolina Hurricanes.
	   Adam Graves also scored two goals, and Jeff Beukeboom, Sean
Pronger and Niklas Sundstrom had two assists apiece for New York.
The six goals fell two shy of the Rangers' record for goals in a
period, set in a 12-1 win over the California Golden Seals in 1971.
	   Carolina gave up six goals in a period for the second time in
its existence.
	   Sami Kapanen, Gary Roberts and Nelson Emerson scored for
Carolina, which beat the Rangers 1-0 on Wednesday night in New
York.
</TEXT>
